    "failureModeShort": "Upper Saloon Recirculation CO2 Sensor INT",
    "failureModeLong": "upper saloon return CO2 sensor not responding The upper saloon return CO2 sensor measures the temperature and CO2 concentration of the returned  air from the upper saloon. The temperature is used in conjunction with the front-end CO2 sensor  within the saloon to maintain a temperature set-point. The CO2 concentration is used solely to modulate the fresh air dampers to keep the CO2 concentration within a defined limit. In the case that the signal from the CO2 sensor is received but the temperature reading or CO2 concentration is invalid, the fault will be set.",
