    "failureModeShort": "Upper Saloon Compressor",
    "failureModeLong": "upper compressor voltage too low The compressor HV circuit incorporates a DC-link capacitor as stipulated by the manufacturer for  transient performance and EMC. A pre-charge relay is used to bring the voltage on the DC-link capacitor to the line voltage prior to closing the main-contactor. During the pre-charge sequence, the voltage is monitored via the compressor CAN link. In the event that the voltage does not rise during the pre-charge phase, the sequence is aborted and reattempted after a period of time. After three aborted cycles, the fault is set.",
    "severity": "INFORMATION",
    "description": "Upper saloon heating and cooling is not possible when this fault is set.",
    "lowCondition": "Compressor does not receive required voltage level after 3 pre-charge attempts.",
    "highCondition": "Compressor receives required voltage level within the bounds of 3 pre-charge attempts.",
