    "highCondition": "Check the CAN-sensor lines (X3/7, X3/4) and plugs to the central ECU for open circuit and physical damage (including check for chafing damage) OR Check the power supply (X3/10, X3/1) of the ESP sensors OR Check connections of the ESP sensors. OR If wiring is OK and failure is still present: OR change the yaw rate sensor, if failure 'steering angle sensor:communication interrupted' is not present OR change the central ECU, if failure 'steering angle sensor:communication interrupted' is present, too.",
